# Why is it called Generative AI?

A system is called **Generative AI** when it creates **new content** such as text, images, audio, videos,
or code instead of only analyzing or classifying existing data.

For example, in an **English-to-Tamil Translation** project:

```
English Sentence
        │
        ▼
Word Embedding (Word2Vec)
        │
        ▼
LSTM / Transformer
        │
        ▼
Generated Tamil Sentence
```

The model does not simply retrieve a stored translation. Instead, it generates the Tamil sentence based on the patterns it learned during training. Since it creates a new sentence, this is called a **generative task**.

