# Difference Between AI, ML, DL, NLP, and GenAI

| Technology                        | Main Purpose                                                       | Example                           |
| --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------- |
| Artificial Intelligence (AI)      | Makes machines perform intelligent tasks.                          | Chess-playing program             |
| Machine Learning (ML)             | Learns patterns from data.                                         | Spam email detection              |
| Deep Learning (DL)                | Learns complex patterns using neural networks.                     | Image recognition                 |
| Natural Language Processing (NLP) | Enables computers to understand and process human language.        | Sentiment analysis                |
| Generative AI (GenAI)             | Generates new content such as text, images, audio, video, or code. | ChatGPT, Gemini, image generators |

---



**Generative AI is not simply NLP plus Deep Learning. 
NLP provides techniques to process human language, while Deep Learning provides neural network models that learn patterns from data. 
When these deep learning models are trained to generate new content—such as text, translations, summaries, images, or code—they are called Generative AI models. 
For example, ChatGPT uses NLP with a Transformer-based deep learning model to generate new text, which is why it is considered a Generative AI system.**














